div.p: 1. left pointer: the first element not equals to 0
2. right pointer: the first element from right not equals 2
3. index: iterate from left to right.
There could be three case for left pointer:
if index pointer is 0, then swap needed, and left and index will move right.
because we are scanning from right, so there is no 2 before index, so after swap, we can safely move right index. But swap with right not the same case
if index pointer is 1, then index move to right and look for next element
if index pointer is 2, then swap with right
current index is 0, then swap with left and move right
current index is 1, then no swap needed, move right
